<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-07-31T18:50:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-04-14T18:51:00-05:00" n="157" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d157">
                    <head>American Residents of Pau</head>
                    <dateline>
                        <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-volume-rules" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1865-07-31T23:59:59+00:09" notBefore="1865-04-15T00:00:00+00:09">undated</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <p rend="flushleft">
                        <hi rend="italic">To His Excellency the Minister of the United States at
                            Paris</hi>:</p>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The undersigned, residents and visitors at
                        Pau, forgetting their political dissensions before such a national calamity
                        as the dastardly murder of the late President, Abraham Lincoln, beg leave
                        most respectfully to convey to your excellency the expression of their
                        horror and indignation at so criminal an act.</p>
                    <p>They earnestly wish, moreover, through the medium of your excellency, to add
                        the testimony of their sympathy, in common with their own countrymen and all
                        the civilized world.</p>
                    <p>They have the honor to be, most respectfully, your obedient servants.</p>
                    <table cols="2" rows="10">
                        <row>
                            <cell>E. RORRUN GRAVES.</cell>
                            <cell>CHAS. RUSH, <hi rend="italic">VICE-ADMIRAL B. M. S</hi>.</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
